  "answer": "Yes, in the maqta (final couplet) of this ghazal, Zauq signs his name (takhallus) explicitly as *Zauq*, contrasting a loveless heart unfavorably with a stone that at least has fire.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/16-ek-sadma-dard-e-dil-se-meri-jaan-par-toh-hai/translation/#p-df8cda).  \n\"O Zauq, a heart that has no fire of love  \nIs worse than stone, which has a fiery core, at least.\"",
